Available for Deployment!

Our tiny archeologists have returned from their expedition to the tiny tank vaults and are proud to present you the ageless classic of tiny tank warfare - Sturmpanzer Mel! Named in honour of the ancient worthy, who for his skill in CAD was awarded the prestigious title of "CADor" - Mel the CADor is your number 1 choice for trench combat, prolonged sieges and general attritional warfare. The sturdy hull is provided with numerous options including:

- two different extra fuel tanks
- trench rails
- roof mounted searchlight

Furthermore our decoration team furnished optional imperial insignia to be affixed on prominent locations of your tank.

Autocannons, Laser Cannons, Heavy Gyrojets and a mighty Siege Howitzer are provided for sponson and hull mounts. The durable casemate can mount either a powerful cannon, long barreled tank killer cannon or a dual laser cannons.

In addition to that a specialized Protector variant is provided fully festooned with anti personnel weaponry for those hectic Mondays.

Furthermore all roof hatches are rendered fully operational so that you can always fulfil your urge to catch that fragrant smell of phosgene in the air.

Sturmpanzer Mel represents an exciting new chassis to be added to our tiny tank offering and is perfect for vehicular combat in 6 to 8mm scales!

This is a collection of pre-constructed hulls of the Auxiliary Heavy Tanks, with and without Dozer Blades and trench rails.

Each combination of main gun and hull gun is included, making it easier to print exactly the hull combination you want without them having to construct the kits. There are a total of 78 hull combinations, and the files for the 4 sponson types.

The main set has been made to be complimentary with 8mm scale battle tanks of a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame.

Ok, so there are many ways to confiture the Malc, so here are a few of them. I did variants based on the combinations of the mainguns (Vanquisher, Battle Cannon, and Double LasCans with 3 different hull guns (lascanon, HvyBolter, Demolisher) and the 2 different sponsons of Autocannons and LasCans.

These STLs have been painstakingly repaired/ filled and then had the underneath scooped out to reduce suction.

Now, if the one you are seeking doesn't quite exist, just open them into 3D builder and cut/paste to your hearts desire. Its pretty easy - plenty of tutorials on the tube of YOU.

These models are all ultimately based on Danny_Cyanide's work. They were reduced in scale and assembled by Korgaan, but had a lot of internal hollow (especially around the sides/ tracks) that needed to be filled. I did a ton of repair work. Other creators have worked on these prior, but I noticed there were still internal hollows, so the ones here should be a better print with a lower chance of resin leakage - it is difficult to take multi-part STLs and assemble a single print model without some stuff missed - so this is not in any way a criticism of those fine works.

There are 8 tanks here:
BattleTurret with AutoCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
BattleTurret with LasCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
BattleTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and HvyBolterHull
DblLasCaneTurret with LasCannonSpn and LascanonHull
VanqTurret with LasCannonSpn and DemolisherHull
VanqTurret with LasCannonSpn and LascanonHull

This posting is not in anyway an invite for "aktually - sniff - blah blah blah" type of comments. People that think that way are typically not the subject matter experts they want to be on the internets. Either get off the internet or if you can do it better - do it.
